**Purpose and Explanation:**

The purpose of my App is to allow a user to be able to enter the date and day, minimum and maximum temperatures for each day, and the weather condition. This information should then be displayed on the app so that anyone is able to see what the minimum and maximum temperatures are for each day/date over the course of seven days. They can also see the average temperature for all of the days displayed, and a detailed view of all the information that was input. You can use the app by starting it up and on the first screen pressing the “Main Screen” button or pressing the close button to close the application. If you navigate to the main screen where you will be able to input all the data for the date, day, minimum temperature, maximum temperature and weather condition for each day/date. Make use of the “Add Input” button after each data entry to add it to the variable arrays. Upon completing your data entry, you can press the view button which will take you to the final screen and display all the information you added, or press the delete button to clear all the data you put in. If you navigate to the final screen, here you will see everything displayed, as well as the average temperature for the total days. You can either return back and re-enter data or go back to the first screen and close the app.
